This is a new recipe for the assignment on Udacity:

Fried Egg -

Ingredients:

-1 egg
-tsp butter or margarine
-(optional) dash of spices such as salt and pepper

Directions:
1. Set small pan on stove at medium temperature.
2. Place butter or margarine in pan to melt. Make sure bottom of pan is covered completely.
3. Crack open egg and add it to pan. Sprinkle some spices on top of egg if desired.
4. Cover pan with lid and wait about 3 minutes to cook. Check on egg for desired doneness. Egg is done when whites of egg are no longer clear and look white. 